{
  "texts": [
    "Examples of such use include Cerina and Duch (2023); Staab et al. (2023).",
    "What these examples have in common is to portray opinion polling powered by Artificial Intelligence and fuelled by Big Data.",
    "Artificial Intelligence refers to \"...a system's ability to interpret external data correctly, to learn from such data, and to use those learnings to achieve specific goals and tasks through flexible adaptation\" (Kaplan and Haenlein 2019; Minsky 1965; McCarthy et al. 2006).",
    "It is an umbrella term encompassing both 'General' foot_0 and 'Narrow' AI foot_1, and we focus on the latter.",
    "Examples of Narrow AI include IBM's Chess-playing 'Deep Blue' (Campbell et al. 2002); Deep-Mind's 'AlphaGo' (Silver et al. 2016); the Starcraft playing 'AlphaStar' (Vinyals et al. 2017); Facebook's image recognition software 'DeepFace' (Taigman et al. 2014)."
  ]
}